         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">1/2/89 ¶  ¶ It is very pleasing to me, dear Dr Hocken, that you think so well of the small volume on "select extratropic plants". ¶ B88.12.01. ¶  ¶ To medical practitioners it is of some use also, as ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">89.02.01</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Thomas Hocken</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">MS-0451-006/008, Archives and Manuscripts, Hocken Library, University of Otago, Dunedin, New Zealand.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">1/2/89</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is very pleasing to me, dear Dr Hocken, that you think so well of the small volume on "select extratropic plants".<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B88.12.01.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>To medical practitioners it is of some use also, as it contains the fairly admisable medicinal plants. Perhaps it will be also a pleasant souvenir of the Congress.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Intercolonial Medical Congress, Melbourne, January 1889.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The Editor of your local paper might perhaps like to have a look on the book.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I trust, when the Austral Assoc for the Advancement of Science will hold its meeting in NZ.,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Australasian Association for the Advancement of Science held its third Congress in Christchurch, NZ, in 1891, and M attended.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I shall have the pleasure of seeing your grand country, - with alps arising almost from the brink of the ocean Sir Joseph Hooker through his visit of NZ during Sir James Ross's antarctic Expedition became the author of the NZ flora;<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. Hooker (1853-5).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>leaving myself in continental Australia such a wide field of research, I never could spare the time for travelling beyond it; indeed I have since 1847, when I came to Australia, never crossed the equator again!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Would there be any chance of inducing any one for a small payment to collect algs (seaweeds) of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">all</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">sorts</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>on your coast, fresh picked up after a storm and merely dried on boards crisply.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hocken obliged; see M to T. Hocken,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>18 March 1889.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
         </div>
